                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1198" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1198" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1198" type="surname" value="LANOLKY"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1198" type="given" value="EDWARD"></interp>EDWARD LANOLKY</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable L</hi> 148.) 1 was on duty in Green<lb></lb>wich park, on the 8th of June, in plain clothes, in company with another officer—I saw Jones take this handkerchief—I had observed the three pri<lb></lb>soners together for half-an-hour, walking and talking together round a ring—I saw Jones take the handkerchief from Mr. Whincup's pocket, he walked away with Harvey—I took them, with the assistance of my fel<lb></lb>low-officer—I found the handkerchief in Harvey's breeches—Markman stood still.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18350615-name-1199" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1199" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1199" type="surname" value="JONES"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18350615-name-1199" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>JOHN JONES</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">police-constable S</hi> 77.) I was on duty in the fair, in plain clothes—I observed the prisoners for about half-an-hour walking through the fair—they went into the park—I observed the prisoner Mark. man attempt several women's pockets, and men's pockets occasionally—they then went round a ring, and had an opportuity of feeling or sound<lb></lb>ing person's pockets I then saw them, behind a gentleman, but did not see them take any thing—I took Jones and Mark man, and my brother<lb></lb>officer took Harvey.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Markman</hi>. I was not in the park above twenty minutes, when that off cer ran up and took them, and then he took me—though I had not pasted five words with them. <hi rend="italic">Witness</hi>. As we were taking them to the watch-house, I saw Markman trying to get somethiug out of his pocket—I searched him, and found nine shillings and four-pence on him.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Markman's Defence.</hi> I went to the fair with my father, and lost him, which was the reason of my being in the park—I had money enough to keep me from doing any thing of this sort.</p>
